docs.abstract: Two major shareholders argued that Apple should head off a potential reckoning by proactively helping parents limit how children use the company’s technology.
docs.snippet: Two major shareholders argued that Apple should head off a potential reckoning by proactively helping parents limit how children use the company’s technology.
docs.lead_paragraph: A pair of investors who say they hold about $2 billion in Apple stock are pushing the company to do more to protect its youngest users from the effects of digital technology.

headline.main: Apple Investors Warn iPhones and Other Technology May Be Hurting Children

docs.abstract: The concert business giant announced that it settled with Songkick for $110 million and an additional undisclosed sum to acquire the company’s technology assets and patents.
docs.snippet: The concert business giant announced that it settled with Songkick for $110 million and an additional undisclosed sum to acquire the company’s technology assets and patents.
docs.lead_paragraph: Two years ago, Songkick, a ticketing start-up that operated out of a loft in Brooklyn, filed an antitrust suit against Live Nation Entertainment, the colossus of the concert business.

headline.main: Live Nation Settles Suit With Ticketing Start-Up, Buying Its Assets
headline.print_headline: Live Nation Settles Lawsuit With Ticketing Start-Up

docs.abstract: Mr. Paul, 22, posted a video that showed a body hanging from a tree in a Japanese forest that is known as a destination for suicide victims.
docs.snippet: Mr. Paul, 22, posted a video that showed a body hanging from a tree in a Japanese forest that is known as a destination for suicide victims.
docs.lead_paragraph: A YouTube star with millions of followers apologized on Monday for posting a video that showed a dead body hanging from a tree in a Japanese forest known as a destination for suicide victims.

headline.main: Logan Paul, YouTube Star, Says Posting Video of Dead Body Was ‘Misguided’
headline.print_headline: YouTube Star Sorry For Video of Corpse

docs.abstract: The toy retailer is another failure of financial engineering, one that could portend a potentially more ominous outlook for private equity in the digital era.
docs.snippet: The toy retailer is another failure of financial engineering, one that could portend a potentially more ominous outlook for private equity in the digital era.
docs.lead_paragraph: The mood in the courtroom was hopeful when Toys “R” Us filed for bankruptcy last September. The company’s lawyer, in the first hearing, played a clip of the retailer’s famous jingle “I’m a Toys ‘R’ Us Kid” and vowed to restore the company’s place in the hearts of millions of American families.

headline.main: Toys ‘R’ Us Case Is Test of Private Equity in Age of Amazon
headline.print_headline: This Toy Story Foreshadowed Its Sad Ending

docs.abstract: Walt Disney Studios hasn’t released a movie that depicts smoking since 2015. Now antismoking activists want that rule extended to all films aimed at young audiences by Fox, which Disney is buying.
docs.snippet: Walt Disney Studios hasn’t released a movie that depicts smoking since 2015. Now antismoking activists want that rule extended to all films aimed at young audiences by Fox, which Disney is buying.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Add cigarettes to the list of things that the family-friendly Walt Disney Company has to figure out as it prepares to integrate the sharper-edged 20th Century Fox movie and television studio.

headline.main: There’s No Smoking in Disney Films. What About When It Owns Fox?
headline.print_headline: When a Smoker Joins the Family

docs.abstract: Given all the changes in the tax code, some people may have too much — or too little — withheld this year. “The message is, you probably want to check.”

docs.abstract: Stocks closed higher on Wednesday after reports showed slumping retail sales but a rate of inflation that exceeded estimates.

headline.main: Wall St. Gains as Investors Weigh Inflation and Retail Data

docs.abstract: Banks have created a variety of risky funds that allow investors to wager against sharp swings in the value of stocks. Those investors are starting to feel some pain.
docs.snippet: Banks have created a variety of risky funds that allow investors to wager against sharp swings in the value of stocks. Those investors are starting to feel some pain.
docs.lead_paragraph: As stocks maintained their smooth and steady climb in recent years, few trades were as alluring, or as profitable, as a bet that volatility as measured by Wall Street’s so-called fear gauge had vanished.

headline.main: Volatility Rattles Stocks, and Investors Who Bet on a Continuing Calm
